        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-22T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-22T18:00:00-05:00" n="815" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d815">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 EW/1–2245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-22T18:00:00-05:00">January 22, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:23 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. In conversation with the Minister for Foreign Affairs this afternoon he
                    reiterated that the exchange of notes he desired would have no <pb facs="1017" n="1003" xml:id="pg_1003"/> effect upon the international situation but he
                    insisted it would be necessary in consideration of the internal political
                    situation as explained in my previous telegrams. For this reason I exchanged
                    notes with him as set forth in the Department’s telegram 55, January 20, 3 p.m.
                    The Minister seemed very pleased with the Department’s wording of the two
                    notes.</p>
                <p>He stated that the President will send a message to the Assembly either this
                    afternoon or tomorrow and that he expects a declaration of war by the Assembly
                    by the end of this week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
